If you check out this post on the Data001 piazza, it looks like prerequisites are being enforced. 

If you're not a declared DS/Stats senior, there is an unfortunately small chance of you getting into the course. For the two semesters it's offered, I dont' think any pure CS majors have gotten in so I'm not sure if anybody has been able to petition.

history.content: I wouldn't expect anyone to get in without prereqs

Could anyone in Data 102 this semester share their opinions on the class and whether anyone has been successful in petitioning for the class as an upper div CS requirement? 

Also, does anyone have any insights on how difficult it is to get into the class as a Senior CS major - it seems hard to get into because the only reserved seats I could possibly qualify for are “ 30 reserved for Students with Enrollment Permission” but I’m not sure how you get enrollment permission. Maybe I would need to email the professors to get enrollment permission!

Does anyone know if the prereq of “EECS 126 or stat 140...” is strictly enforced in order to get into the class, or it’s just suggested? Would CS 70 give enough of a probability background or not?
